headlines.description: Matthew Wilson scored 16 and Army overcame 25 turnovers to beat American 58-54 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Army holds American scoreless down the stretch for 58-54 win

headlines.description: Max Mahoney had 22 points on 9-of-14 shooting and freshman Walter Whyte had his first career double-double to help Boston University beat Lehigh 92-81 on Monday night for coach Joe Jones' 200th career win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mahoney, Whyte help Boston U beat Lehigh 92-81

headlines.description: Zach Thomas scored 25 points and grabbed 13 rebounds, Nana Foulland had 20 points, 11 boards and three blocks, and Bucknell beat Lafayette 80-75 in overtime on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thomas, Foulland combine for 45 points, Bucknell wins in OT

headlines.description: Martaveous McKnight had 24 points, six rebounds and nine assists on Monday night and Arkansas-Pine Bluff beat Alabama State 94-68 for its third win in a row.
headlines.shortLinkText: McKnight leads Arkansas-Pine Bluff over Alabama State 94-68

headlines.description: Austin Butler scored all of his 12 points in a second-half run by Holy Cross and Jacob Grandison finished with 10 points, on 4-of-6 shooting, to help the Crusaders beat Loyola (Md.) 63-57 on Monday night and snap a five-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Holy Cross snaps 5-game skid, beats Loyola (Md) 63-57

headlines.description: Brandon Tabb scored 28 points, with seven 3-pointers, and grabbed eight rebounds to help Bethune-Cookman beat Maryland-Eastern Shore 89-84 on Monday night.

Chad Andrews-Fulton scored the go-ahead layup with 12 seconds left in double overtime and Coppin State beat Florida A&M 79-78 on Monday night, ending the Eagles' 20-game losing streak dating to last season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coppin State ends 20-game slide, beats Florida A&M in 2OT

headlines.description: Denzel Keyes scored 17 points on 8-of-10 shooting and Devonte Boykins added 16 points, including four 3-pointers, to help North Carolina A&T beat Delaware State 76-66 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Keyes scores 17, NC A&T beats Delaware State 76-66

headlines.description: Tiwian Kendley made a go-ahead floater with 6.4 seconds remaining and Morgan State beat Savannah State 89-88 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kendley scores 33, Morgan State rallies by Savannah St 89-88

headlines.description: Raasean Davis scored 13 of his 23 points in the second half including a pair of free throws in the final minute that helped North Carolina Central hold off Norfolk State 64-63 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: North Carolina Central rallies past Norfolk State 64-63

headlines.description: Senior Jason Perry-Murray had his second career double-double and Anthony Gaston scored 16 points to help Grambling beat Alcorn State 72-61 on Monday night to snap a five-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Perry-Murray's double-double helps Grambling beat Alcorn St.

headlines.description: Julian Walters had 14 points on Monday night and Alabama A&M beat Mississippi Valley State 65-55, making the Delta Devils the last winless team in Division I this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Alabama A&M beats Mississippi Valley State 65-55

headlines.description: Lemmie Howard scored seven of his 12 points in the final four minutes and Maurice Rivers made 4 of 4 free throws in the closing seconds to help Jackson State beat Southern 65-61 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rivers, Howard lead Jackson St. to 65-61 win over Southern

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
